                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#63r">Fol. 63r</locus>: Note on the land charter issued by King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89) to May ʾAnbäsa. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic; the note concerns the gwǝlt to May ʾAnbäsa donated by King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#131rc">Fol. 131rc</locus>: Donation note (?)  <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is effaced. The name of the donor Täklä Wängel and the name of his wife are still readable; the note contained also the name of the scribe, written in red ink, now unreadable.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Incomplete list of the items owned by the monastery, crudely written in blue pen: fol. 1v. &#xD;
- The title ብስራተ፡ አብ፡ ትሩፍ፡ is carefully written in red ink on ol. 1v. &#xD;
- A strip of parchment is inserted (?): fol. 7r.&#xD;
- Small cross on the left margin of the first column of fol. 94r.</item>
                     </list>
